text:
Hey everyone, I know there’s been a TON of announcements, so I wouldn’t say this unless it was important! Opening social for the Adam Smith Society TOMORROW at 5:30pm!
1. How do I RSVP? 
Go to <#C0499MYJVPZ|adam-smith-society> channel and react to this thread I shared here!
2. WHY should I RSVP?
If you, a) want to eventually listen to interesting speakers, b) network with classmates, or c) enjoy great discussion and food around free market principles!
3. WHAT is the commitment level?
ABSOLUTELY NONE! This is a no fee club, and contrary to Megan Lesa’s comments, you get WAY MORE than you paid for! Partially because we’re funded by the Manhattan Institute from the East Coast
4. BUT “I don’t want to get notifications from a channel that I may not have time to pay attention to!”
If you look at how to use slack, you’ll see that you can mute notifications from specific channels. 2nd year pro-tip for anyone who’s experiencing stimuli overload after mid terms and the first month and a half of the program have “humbled”/ abased you and your sense of competency.

:volleyball: Volleyball Night :volleyball:

Join us for some fun and friendly volleyball games on Friday, the 27th, from 6-8 pm at the SFH building. It's a great opportunity to unwind and have a blast. Whether you're a pro or just looking to have a good time, everyone is welcome! We have 2 courts reserved for us! 

See you all there!
